modules.description: Provides resampling of audio data using the libsamplerate library, including functions for initializing resamplers, processing audio buffers, and adjusting sample rates. Works with raw audio data represented as arrays of floating-point numbers. Used to convert audio files between different sampling rates while maintaining quality during playback or processing.

Converts audio data between different sampling rates using specified converter algorithms, handling input and output buffers with precise control over sample offsets and channel counts. Operates on float arrays and bigarrays, supporting both in-place and allocated buffer processing. Processes audio streams with adjustable ratios, suitable for real-time resampling or batch processing of audio files.
